# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for protected paths.
#
# GitHub only resolves real GitHub identities here, so this file lists
# the repository owner only. The squad personas (Maya, Priya, Diego,
# Sam, Noor, Yuki, Scribe) referenced in `.squad/team.md` are role
# labels, not GitHub accounts; routing to squad members happens via
# `squad:{member}` labels and the workflows under
# `.github/workflows/squad-*.yml`, not via CODEOWNERS.
#
# Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Pattern syntax matches gitignore. Last matching pattern wins.

# Default owner for everything not matched below.
*                                   @martinopedal

# Plan, schema, and squad governance — Lead-equivalent review (the
# repo owner) is mandatory. These files set scope and contracts for
# the whole codebase.
/docs/plan.md                       @martinopedal
/docs/schema.md                     @martinopedal
/.squad/                            @martinopedal
/.github/copilot-instructions.md    @martinopedal

# Security-relevant surfaces. Maps to `squad:security-reviewer`
# (Noor)'s adversarial-pass charter; until that role is mapped to a
# real GitHub account, the repository owner stands in.
/SECURITY.md                        @martinopedal
/.github/CODEOWNERS                 @martinopedal
/.github/dependabot.yml             @martinopedal
/.github/workflows/                 @martinopedal
/src/finops_assess/collectors/      @martinopedal
/src/finops_assess/engine.py        @martinopedal

# Pricing and SKU catalogue — pricing edits are 🔴 in the squad fit
